      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-06-09T09:19:57Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think its better to have `i_maxThreadsPerChassis` as a member variable of `ThreadManager` class, so that `Manager` can configure `maxThreadsPerChassis` as needed while constructing `ThreadManager` object.\n\nThis can also help to limit number of threads in reset-reload scenario.",
      "revId": "58520f3002da3d9612387d3a115b594b05c2d1bb",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "74a30230_e4568c73",
        "filename": "vpd-manager/include/thread_manager.hpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 182,
      "author": {
        "id": 1001932
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-06-09T10:21:36Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think we should avoid deciding i_maxThreadsPerChassis during ThreadManager object creation itself.\n\nCurrently, the value is derived dynamically based on the total maximum threads and the number of chassis present:\n\nMAX_THREADS / chassisCount\n\nSo the per-chassis thread limit may vary depending on the system configuration in the future(based on how many chassis are present). Passing it as a parameter keeps the API flexible and allows the caller to decide the appropriate value based on runtime conditions.",
      "parentUuid": "045e54dc_53944d90",
      "revId": "58520f3002da3d9612387d3a115b594b05c2d1bb",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    }
